cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite the methods paper and (when available) the Software Impacts companion paper."
type: software
title: "iSAGE: Iterative Sparse Annotation Guided by Expert"
abstract: >-
  iSAGE is an integrated platform for semantic segmentation that lets a
  domain expert click on pixels where the current model is confidently
  wrong. The Error-Weighted Dice Loss amplifies the gradient at those
  clicks during retraining, and the JSON annotation record itself is the
  dataset — no propagation, pseudo-labels, or CRF refinement between the
  click and the gradient.
